This paper is about representation learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on disentangled representation learning, which is a subfield of representation learning. The paper proposes a new assumption about the relation between data and disentangled representations via mutual information. This assumption is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper is primarily focused on unsupervised learning of disentangled representations, we can expect that cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
